            <thetext>The testsaslauthd in Cyrus SASL 2.1.12 requires that one specifies the
password on the command line.  Even if this is purely for testing, there
should be a mode where the password is read from the terminal without echo
(or from a file if need be) to avoid revealing passwords to users that
happen to invoke ps at the wrong time.</thetext>
